bibl.note:
. For the biblical passage referenced by this chapter heading see the following heading and the critical note in the analogue's apparatus.
                        In Sg1, the original rubricated marginal numeral, now partially faded, appears as 9;
                        this is a result of the error in the marginal numbering that began at ch. 5 (see above).

. Cfr. Lv 14:2 Hic est ritus leprosi quando mundandus est adducetur ad sacerdotem :
                        VL 100 haec lex leprosi quacumque die mundus erit et adducetur ad sacerdotem;
                        Lv 14:8 purificatusque ingredietur castra : VL 100 et mundus erit et post haec introibit in castra.
